changeMintPrice(uint256).details: Validates that the new price doesn't conflict with ongoing auctionsUpdates the minimum bid change amount proportionally (2.5% of new price)Cannot be called if current auction has bids below the new priceThe logic is designed to prevent the winner's final bid from being lower than      the basic mint price, which would make minting impossible

params._newPrice: New basic mint price in wei

checkUpkeep(bytes).details: performData encodes the auctionId to be used by performUpkeep for execution.

returns.performData: Encoded data to be passed to performUpkeep, containing the auctionId.
returns.upkeepNeeded: Boolean indicating whether upkeep should be performed.

claimFailedRefunds().details: Reverts if caller has no failed refunds to claimEmits YoyoAuction__BidderRefunded event on successful claim

claimNftForWinner(uint256).details: Used as a fallback when the automatic minting in _closeAuction() and claimNftForWinner() failsIf the NFT was already minted to the contract, it will be transferred. If not, the contract will mint it and transfer.

params._auctionId: The ID of the auction for which the winner is claiming the NFT.

constructor.details: Contract constructor that sets the deployer as the ownerInitializes auction counter to 0The NFT contract address must be set separately after deployment

getAuctionCounter().details: This value also represents the ID of the latest auction.Used as a reference key for `s_auctionsFromAuctionId` mapping and in functions like `getCurrentAuction` and `changeMintPrice`.

getAuctionFromAuctionId(uint256).details: Includes pricing, timing, current bids, and auction state.Used in multiple parts of the contract for bid validation, auction status checks, and Chainlink upkeep logic.

params._auctionId: ID of the auction to retrieve

getCurrentAuction().details: Fetches auction data using the current auction counter.Used in functions like `getCurrentAuctionPrice` and `changeMintPrice` to operate on the most recent auction.

returns._0: AuctionStruct Full data of the latest auction

getCurrentAuctionPrice().details: For English auctions: highest bid + minimum increment.For Dutch auctions: calculated based on elapsed time and price drop intervals.Used in `placeBidOnDutchAuction` to validate the bid amount and ensure the winner pays the current fair price.Reverts if no auction is currently open.

returns._0: uint256 Current auction price in wei
uint256 Number of price drop intervals (48)

getDutchAuctionStartPriceMultiplier().details: Starting price = basic mint price * multiplier.Used in `openNewDutchAuction` and `restartAuction` to determine starting price for Dutch auctions.

returns._0: uint256 Dutch auction start price multiplier

getElegibilityForClaimingNft(uint256,add.details: Returns true if the caller has an unclaimed NFT for the given auction.

params._auctionId: The ID of the auction to check eligibility for.
params._claimer: The address of the potential claimer.

returns.eligible: True if the caller can claim the NFT, false otherwise.

getFailedRefundAmount(address).details: Used to track and allow bidders to claim any failed refunds

params._bidder: Address of the bidder to check

returns._0: uint256 Amount of failed refunds in wei
uint256 Grace period duration in seconds (21600)

getMinimumBidChangeAmount().details: For English auctions, this is set to 2.5% of the basic mint price.Used in `placeBidOnEnglishAuction` to validate bid increments and in auction initialization.

returns._0: uint256 Minimum bid increment in wei

getMinimumBidChangePercentage().details: Returns MINIMUM_BID_INCREMENT_PERCENTAGE constant (25 per-mille = 2.5%)This percentage is applied to the basic mint price to determine s_minimumBidChangeAmount

returns._0: uint256 Minimum bid increment percentage in per-mille (25 = 2.5%)
uint256 Minimum possible mint price in wei (40 wei with current constants)

getNftContract().details: This address must be set before auctions can be created.Used throughout the contract to call NFT-specific functions through the IYoyoNft interface.

returns._0: address Address of the NFT collection contract

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: Implements the ERC721Receiver interface to accept safe transfers and mints.

params.data: Additional data with no specified format.
params.from: The address which previously owned the token.
params.tokenId: The NFT identifier which is being transferred.

returns._0: selector The selector to confirm the token transfer.

openNewAuction(uint256,uint8).details: Only the contract owner can call this function.Validates the NFT contract, token ID, and ensures no overlapping auctions.Once the checks are completed, it will call the initialization function specific to the chosen auction type.After the execution of the type-specific function is finished, it will emit the auction opened event.

params._auctionType: The type of auction (ENGLISH or DUTCH).
params._tokenId: The ID of the NFT to be auctioned.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

performUpkeep(bytes).details: Decodes the auctionId and auctionEndTime from performData.Reverts if `checkUpkeep` returns `upkeepNeeded = false`.Only Chainlink Automation or owner can call this function within the grace period.To avoid DOS if Chainlink goes down, after the grace period anyone can call this function.

params.performData: Encoded data containing the auctionId to process.

placeBidOnAuction(uint256).details: Uses reentrancy guard to prevent reentrancy attacksValidates auction existence and state before processing bidDelegates to specific bid processing functions based on auction type

params._auctionId: ID of the auction to bid on

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setChainlinkForwarder(address).details: Can only be set once by the owner

params._chainlinkForwarder: The address of the Chainlink Automation forwarder

setNftContract(address).details: the NFT collection address cannot be set in the constructor and must be set immediately after deployment.

params._yoyoNftAddress: the address of the nft collection smart contract

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

changeMintPrice(uint256).notice: Allows the owner to change the basic mint price for future auctions

checkUpkeep(bytes).notice: Called by Chainlink Keepers to check if upkeep is needed.Retrieves the latest auction using s_auctionCounter.Checks if the auction is currently open and if its end time has passed.upkeepNeeded is true only if the auction has ended but is still marked as open.

claimFailedRefunds().notice: Allows users to claim ETH from failed refund attemptsWhen a refund to a previous bidder fails (e.g., contract recipient),         the amount is stored in a mapping for later manual claim

claimNftForWinner(uint256).notice: Allows the auction winner to manually claim their NFT if automatic minting or transfer failed.

getAuctionCounter().notice: Returns the total number of auctions created so far

getAuctionDuration().notice: Returns the duration of each auction in hours

getAuctionFromAuctionId(uint256).notice: Returns all information about a specific auction by its ID

getChainlinkForwarderAddress().notice: Returns the address of the Chainlink Forwarder

getCurrentAuctionPrice().notice: Returns the current price of the ongoing auction

getDutchAuctionNumberOfIntervals().notice: Returns the number of price drop intervals in Dutch auctions

getDutchAuctionStartPriceMultiplier().notice: Returns the multiplier used to calculate Dutch auction starting price

getElegibilityForClaimingNft(uint256,add.notice: Checks if the caller is eligible to claim an NFT for a specific auction.

getFailedRefundAmount(address).notice: Returns the amount of failed refunds for a specific bidder

getGracePeriod().notice: Returns the grace period duration for manual auction closure

getMinimumBidChangeAmount().notice: Returns the minimum amount required to outbid the current highest bid

getMinimumBidChangePercentage().notice: Returns the percentage used to calculate the minimum bid increment

getMinimumPossibleMintPrice().notice: Returns the minimum allowed mint price for NFTs

getNftContract().notice: Returns the address of the NFT contract managed by this auction

getPercentageDenominator().notice: Returns the denominator used for percentage calculations

getUpkeepId().notice: Returns the upkeep ID associated with this contract

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.notice: Allows this contract to safely receive ERC721 tokens (NFTs).

openNewAuction(uint256,uint8).notice: Opens a new auction for a given NFT token, with a specified auction type.

If instead thereis no higher bidder, the auction will be restarted.

placeBidOnAuction(uint256).notice: Allows users to place bids on active auctions

setChainlinkForwarder(address).notice: Sets the Chainlink Automation forwarder address
